sequenceDiagram
    participant User as Data Scientist
    participant Dashboard as odh-dashboard<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS
    participant GW as Gateway API<br/>data-science-gateway<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Notebook as Notebook Workbench<br/>Jupyter/Code Server
    participant DSP as DSP API Server<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Argo as Argo Workflow Controller
    participant MLMD as ml-metadata<br/>8081/TCP gRPC
    participant S3 as S3 Storage<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant ModelReg as Model Registry<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS
    participant KServe as KServe Controller
    participant ODHModel as odh-model-controller
    participant vLLM as vLLM Runtime<br/>8000/TCP HTTP
    participant EPP as llm-d EPP<br/>ext-proc
    participant KVCache as llm-d KV-Cache
    participant FMSOrch as FMS Guardrails<br/>8034/TCP HTTP
    participant Detectors as Guardrails Detectors
    participant Prometheus as Prometheus
    participant WVA as Workload Variant<br/>Autoscaler

    Note over User,WVA: Workflow 1: Model Training to Deployment

    User->>GW: Access Dashboard<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS
    GW->>Dashboard: Forward<br/>HTTPS/8443, kube-rbac-proxy
    User->>GW: Open Notebook<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS
    GW->>Notebook: Forward<br/>HTTPS, kube-auth-proxy OAuth2

    Notebook->>S3: Save training data/model<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+

    User->>DSP: Create Pipeline Run<br/>HTTPS/8443, SAR auth
    DSP->>Argo: Create Workflow CR
    Argo->>Argo: Execute pipeline steps as pods
    Argo->>MLMD: Log artifacts + metadata<br/>gRPC/8081
    Argo->>S3: Store pipeline artifacts<br/>HTTPS/443
    Argo-->>DSP: Report status via persistence agent

    User->>ModelReg: Register model version<br/>HTTPS/8443, kube-rbac-proxy
    ModelReg-->>User: Model metadata stored

    Note over User,WVA: Workflow 2: Model Serving

    User->>KServe: Create InferenceService CR<br/>via kubectl/dashboard
    KServe->>vLLM: Deploy serving runtime pod
    KServe->>ODHModel: Reconcile event
    ODHModel->>GW: Create HTTPRoute for inference
    ODHModel->>Prometheus: Create ServiceMonitor

    Note over User,WVA: Workflow 3: LLM Inference with Guardrails

    User->>GW: POST /v1/chat/completions<br/>HTTPS/443, Bearer Token
    GW->>FMSOrch: Forward request<br/>HTTP/8034
    FMSOrch->>Detectors: Input rail check<br/>(HAP, PII detection)
    Detectors-->>FMSOrch: Detection results
    FMSOrch->>GW: Forward to inference<br/>HTTP
    GW->>EPP: ext-proc filter
    EPP->>KVCache: Query KV-cache scores<br/>gRPC
    KVCache-->>EPP: Cache-aware routing decision
    EPP-->>GW: Route to optimal pod
    GW->>vLLM: Inference request<br/>HTTP/8000
    vLLM-->>GW: Generated response
    GW-->>FMSOrch: Response
    FMSOrch->>Detectors: Output rail check
    Detectors-->>FMSOrch: Detection results
    FMSOrch-->>User: Filtered response

    Note over User,WVA: Workflow 4: LLM-Aware Autoscaling

    vLLM->>Prometheus: Export KV cache + queue metrics
    WVA->>Prometheus: Query vLLM metrics<br/>(KV cache util, queue depth)
    Prometheus-->>WVA: Metrics data
    WVA->>WVA: Calculate desired_replicas
    WVA->>Prometheus: Emit scaling metric
    Note right of WVA: HPA/KEDA reads metric<br/>and scales deployment

    Note over User,WVA: Workflow 5: Model Evaluation

    User->>Dashboard: Create evaluation job
    Dashboard->>Dashboard: POST /api eval-hub
    Note right of Dashboard: eval-hub creates K8s Job<br/>with lm-evaluation-harness
    Dashboard->>vLLM: Evaluation queries<br/>(167+ benchmarks)
    vLLM-->>Dashboard: Evaluation results
    Dashboard->>ModelReg: Log evaluation metrics
